    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card frames the task as reproducing chromVAR on 'example_counts dataset', but the paper does not describe a specific example dataset by that name. The paper uses multiple datasets (K562, hematopoietic cells, AML, etc.) but no 'example_counts' is mentioned.",
        "The card focuses on the structure of output objects (chromVARDeviations, RangedSummarizedExperiment), which is a software engineering / API documentation concern. The paper is a methods paper describing the algorithm and biological applications, not a software tutorial or API reference.",
        "The card's emphasis on accessor functions (deviations(), deviationScores()) suggests a vignette or tutorial context, but the paper does not document these specific function signatures."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:36:11.982797+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "chromVAR, a versatile R package for analyzing sparse chromatin accessibility data by measuring the gain or loss of chromatin accessibility within sets of genomic features while controlling for known technical biases in epigenomic data... we have developed chromVAR... to identify transcription factor (TF) motifs that define different cell types and vary within populations",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly addresses ranking motifs by variability and identifying differential motifs between cell types. The variability metric is defined as 'the standard deviation of the z-scores across the cells or samples'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-nmeth-4401",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How can motifs be ranked by their variability in chromatin accessibility across cell populations, and which motifs show statistically significant differential deviation between distinct cell types?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:36:29.594474+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The variability of a TF motif across samples or cells was determined by computing the standard deviation of the z-scores across the cells or samples. The expected value of this metric is one if the motif peak sets are no more variable than the background peak sets for that motif.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms standard deviation of z-scores and comparison to threshold of 1, but no explicit mention of bootstrap confidence intervals in the passages provided. The paper does not detail bootstrap CI computation in the visible methods sections.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-nmeth-4401",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Ranked variability data frame with motif names, standard deviation of z-scores, bootstrap confidence intervals, and p-values for variability > 1",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:36:29.594474+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For determining differentially accessible motifs between AML LSC and blast cells, an unequal variances t-test (two-sided) was used on the bias corrected deviations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes differential analysis using t-tests on bias-corrected deviations, but the specific example is AML LSC vs blast cells, not GM vs H1 cell types. The methodology is present but the specific cell type comparison (GM vs H1) is not explicitly mentioned in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-nmeth-4401",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
