      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we have developed chromVAR, a versatile R package for analyzing sparse chromatin accessibility data by measuring the gain or loss of chromatin accessibility within sets of genomic features while controlling for known technical biases in epigenomic data... We show that chromVAR can be used to identify transcription factor (TF) motifs that define different cell types and vary within populations",
      "asbval:note": "Directly supported; paper explicitly states chromVAR identifies TF motifs that vary within populations",
