    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/method-comparison-statistical-summarization/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "chromVAR may also be applied to a collection of kmers\u2014DNA sequences of a specific length k\u2014in order to perform an unbiased analysis of DNA sequence features that correlate with chromatin accessibility variation across the cells or samples... The clustering accuracy using the bias corrected deviations is also largely preserved after downsampling, and compares favorably to clustering using PCA or other peak-based approaches",
      "asbval:note": "The paper does apply chromVAR to kmers and compares clustering accuracy favorably to PCA, but this is not a cross-method benchmark with compiled metrics and summary statistics. chromVAR is the primary subject of validation, not one of multiple methods being ranked via statistical summarization.",
